tldr: The user wanted to add a database for questionnaire responses, a client
  dashboard, and authentication to their sleep questionnaire application. The
  assistant implemented a Prisma-backed PostgreSQL database (NeonDB), a simple
  password-protected admin dashboard with CSV export, and updated the
  questionnaire form to save data.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by integrating a database for storing responses, developing a
  client-accessible dashboard, and implementing an authentication mechanism. The
  assistant conducted a thorough codebase evaluation, identifying the absence of
  a response database, CSV export, an admin dashboard, and an authentication
  system. Following user clarification, a plan was formulated to use NeonDB with
  Prisma for database management, implement a straightforward password-based
  authentication, and combine demographic data fields. The implementation
  involved updating data models, creating API endpoints for saving, retrieving,
  and exporting responses as CSV, building a login page and an admin dashboard,
  and integrating the database save functionality directly into the
  questionnaire form submission process.
